      <text>8.1.18 (Given geo sequence, decide its properties)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>The geometric sequence defined by \(\displaystyle u_n={@a@}({@r@})^{n-1}\) is:</p><p>[[input:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p><p>and is: [[input:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]] [[validation:ans2]]<br></p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p></p><p>The geometric sequence has first term {@a@} and common ratio {@r@}.</p><p>Since the common ratio is {@["negative","","positive"][signum(r)+2]@}, the terms of the sequence will {@["be alternating in sign","","all be of the same sign"][signum(r)+2]@}. Because \(|{@r@}|&gt;1\), the size of the terms is increasing in absolute value, too.</p><p>So the sequence is {@sdowncase(corr1)@} and&nbsp;{@sdowncase(corr2)@}.</p><br><p></p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
